#!/bin/env bash

# Input for the note title
read -p "Enter the title of your note: " title

# Format the date and title into the filename
formatted_date=$(date +'%Y%m%d%H%M%S')
filename="$formatted_date - $title.md"

# Create the new note file with the template
cat <<EOL > "$HOME/Documents/notes/$filename"
# $title

## Introduction

Provide a brief introduction to the topic of your note.

## Conclusion

Summarize the key points or findings of your note.

## References

If you reference any sources, include them here.

## Related Notes

You can link to other related notes using Markdown links.

- [Link to Related Note 1](related-note-1.md)

- [Link to Related Note 2](related-note-2.md)
EOL
